Rule Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper describes the use of SFOIL, a descendant of FOIL, which is a top-down ILP system that uses the covering approach and advanced search strategies to learn rules from data. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present in the text as the paper mentions the use of the advanced stochastic search heuristic in SFOIL, which is a probabilistic method for searching the space of possible rules.
